rules: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

data.name: Great Ball
rules: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. You may reveal a Pokémon you find there and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

data.name: Ultra Ball
rules: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
You can use this card only if you discard 2 other cards from your hand.\nSearch your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

data.name: Switch

data.name: Pokémon Catcher
rules: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

data.name: Exp. Share
rules: You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
"When your Active Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponents Pokémon, you may move a Basic Energy from that Pokémon to the Pokémon this card is attached to."
